  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nGraduate study at GWU combined analytics coursework with applied project delivery and concurrent assistantship roles, spanning machine learning, data engineering, and sports analytics.\n\n## Workflow\n\nProjects moved from data collection and cleaning through feature engineering, modeling, validation, and visualization, while assistantship work added teaching support and technical-systems operations alongside the degree.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **Machine learning:** applied ML, deep learning, and statistical modeling across graduate projects with validation-driven workflows.\n- **Data engineering:** large-scale distributed processing with Spark and Databricks over multi-million-record datasets.\n- **Sports analytics:** player-valuation and comparison modeling with feature reduction and interactive Dash/Plotly dashboards.\n- **Project management:** coordinated scope, timelines, and deliverables across multiple concurrent projects.\n- **Assistantship exposure:** teaching assistance with LLM-assisted grading support and technical-systems/operational analysis.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nProduced a broad applied-analytics portfolio across ML, data engineering, and visualization, backed by graduate-scale delivery and hands-on assistantship experience during the degree."
